<p>The <code>while</code> tag provides looping while a condition is true.</p>

<h2>Basic While Loop</h2>
<pre>{open}set counter=1{close}
{open}while $counter <= 5{close}
  Item {open}$counter{close}
  {open}increment $counter{close}
{open}/while{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
{set counter=1}
<ul>
{while $counter <= 5}
  <li>Item {$counter}</li>
  {increment $counter}
{/while}
</ul>

<h2>Countdown</h2>
<pre>{open}set n=5{close}
{open}while $n > 0{close}
  {open}$n{close}...
  {open}decrement $n{close}
{open}/while{close}
Liftoff!</pre>
<p>Result: {set n=5}{while $n > 0}{$n}... {decrement $n}{/while}Liftoff!</p>

<h2>Building a List</h2>
<pre>{open}set i=1{close}
{open}while $i <= 3{close}
  &lt;div&gt;Box {open}$i{close}&lt;/div&gt;
  {open}increment $i{close}
{open}/while{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
{set i=1}
{while $i <= 3}
<div style="border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px; margin:2px;">Box {$i}</div>
{increment $i}
{/while}

<h2>Powers of 2</h2>
<pre>{open}set val=1{close}
{open}while $val <= 64{close}
  {open}$val{close}
  {open}set val={open}echo $val * 2{close}{close}
{open}/while{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {set val=1}{while $val <= 64}{$val} {set val={echo $val * 2}}{/while}</p>
